# Phase 6A Final Runtime Verification

Do not modify architecture.

Do not introduce new features.

Run the development server and perform a runtime verification of the implemented SEO foundation.

## Verify these pages

- Home
- About
- Services
- Property
- Community Projects
- Case Studies
- Insights
- Careers
- Contact
- Privacy Notice
- Cookie Notice
- Accessibility
- Complaints
- Terms

## Browser checks

For at least these page types:

- Standard page (About)
- Listing page (Services or Insights)
- Compliance page (Privacy Notice)

Inspect the rendered HTML source.

Confirm:

- `<title>`
- `<meta name="description">`
- `<meta property="og:title">`
- `<meta property="og:description">`
- `<meta property="og:image">` (only when available)
- `<meta property="og:url">`
- `<link rel="canonical">`
- `<meta name="robots">`

Verify:

- No duplicate tags
- No empty tags
- No malformed URLs
- No missing canonical
- No Blade exceptions
- No console errors
- No broken public routes

## Deliverable

Report only:

- Runtime verification status
- Pages verified
- Issues found
- Issues fixed (if any)
- Remaining issues
- Production ready: Yes / No

Do not make speculative improvements.

Do not begin Phase 6B.